      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KINGSBRAE MAGGIE (3) crossed over from out wide but caught the leaders turning before drawing clear to score (18.00) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Well placed and will be tough to beat. ROCKY BELL (2) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.68 beating Just Too Easy. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Expecting another bold showing. ULTRA SPECIAL (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has hit the frame the last two runs, the latest when third (18.02) at this track. Well placed and gets her chance. CROSSED TOES (7) is likely to have admirers.",
